	and day to day use of
	<span class="emphasis"><em>FreeBSD 8.4-RELEASE</em></span> and
	<span class="emphasis"><em>FreeBSD 9.1-RELEASE</em></span>.  This
	manual is a <span class="emphasis"><em>work in progress</em></span> and is the
	work of many individuals.  As such, some sections may become
	dated and require updating.  If you are interested in helping
	out with this project, send email to the <a class="ulink" href="http://lists.FreeBSD.org/mailman/listinfo/freebsd-doc" target="_top">FreeBSD documentation project mailing list</a>.  The latest
	version of this document is always available from the
	<a class="ulink" href="http://www.FreeBSD.org/" target="_top">FreeBSD web site</a>
	(previous versions of this handbook can be obtained from
	<a class="ulink" href="http://docs.FreeBSD.org/doc/" target="_top">http://docs.FreeBSD.org/doc/</a>).  It may
	also be downloaded in a variety of formats and compression
	options from the
	<a class="ulink" href="ftp://ftp.FreeBSD.org/pub/FreeBSD/doc/" target="_top">FreeBSD
	  FTP server</a> or one of the numerous
	<a class="link" href="mirrors-ftp.html" title="A.2. FTP Sites">mirror sites</a>.  If you would
	prefer to have a hard copy of the handbook, you can purchase
	one at the
	<a class="ulink" href="http://www.freebsdmall.com/" target="_top">FreeBSD Mall</a>.
	You may also want to
	<a class="ulink" href="../../../../search/index.html" target="_top">search the
	  handbook</a>.</p></div></div></div><div xmlns="http://www.w3.org/TR/xhtml1/transitional" class="docformatnavi">
